Chima Azubuike, Gombe The Governor of Gombe State, Inuwa Yahaya, has ordered an investigation into the inferno, which engulfed the popular Idi Mall owned by the Gombe Local Government Council. The fire disaster, which occurred on Saturday, resulted in the loss of property worth millions of naira. While sympathising with the victims, the governor ordered relevant agencies to investigate the cause of the inferno and submit a report to him. He said, “We are grateful to God that there was no loss of life to the unfortunate incident. “Relevant government agencies are to investigate the remote and immediate causes of the inferno with a view to preventing future occurrences as well as assess the extent of damage and property loss.” Copyright PUNCH.
